cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper presents a large-scale dataset of eye-images captured using a VR head-mounted display, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) communities. The dataset can also be used for machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of corneal topography, which is a technique used in ophthalmology and optometry, indicating a potential relevance to graphics (cs.GR) as well.
